<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>New Messageboard</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>I had hoped to take over The Dojo board from Sensei, so that we would have access to all the information already on it, but unfortunately I am unable to get hold of him, so I bit the bullet and made my own.</p><p>Clicking on the <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508">Message Boards</a> link over in the left panel will take you straight to it. Once at the board, clicking on the logo at the top of the page will bring you back here.</p><p>Hope to see you all there!</p></FONT></ul>

<p><FONT size=5 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><b>My email link</b></FONT><br>
<FONT size=2 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Submitted by <a href="mailto:zadkiel@monkly-business.com">Zadkiel</a></FONT></p>
<ul>
<FONT size=3 face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#8b1a1a"><p>OK, this is gonna be a mini-rant I'm afraid, but it has to be said.</p><p>My email is being flooded. In the past 3 days, I have had over 300 emails from monks. Now, those that are related to the site, I have no problem with, infact I welcome them with open arms, the site can only be great if YOU make it great.. BUT, I'm getting a lot of off-topic email, and I want to say something about it.</p><p><ul><LI>NO, I dont care that you have a level 374 druid, NO, I dont care that you now have a level 6 monk, NO, I am not going to tell you which is better, Tranquil Staff or Runed Fighter Staff, and YES, I did just delete your email.<LI>NO, I will not twink you.<LI>NO, I will not powerlevel you.<LI>NO, I'm wearing it, I'm not going to sell it.</p></ul>Well, that just answered about 50 emails, I feel better now.</p>The last type of email I am not going to reply to, I feel kinda bad about. I'm talking about legitimate newbies looking for answers to questions, and not finding the answer on the site (Yet). I'm talking about the <i>'Someone told me that wearing reinforced armor was bad, because it was so heavy, but I saved up for 5 levels to buy it, and I'm still 40 weight under my maximum, thats ok isn't it?</i> types of email.</p><p>The reason I am not going to answer them, is:</p><p><OL type=1><LI>I don't have the time<LI>I don't want set up a precedent, and turn my email link into a 'Ask Uncle Zadkiel' Kind of deal.</OL></p><p>For those of you wanting answers to those types of questions, please click on the <a href="/mb/">Messageboard</a> link, and ask your questions there. Don't feel embarrassed, we were all newbies once, and we are a pretty good bunch over there, you won't get flamed, and who knows, you might get the posting bug</p></FONT></ul>

<br><br>
